My daughter loves this app!! Beautiful graphics and lots of fun. There is a bug at the very end of level six.  She has gone through it about three times , after having collected all the butterflies and when she gets to the end she jumps on the rock with fuddle and Mia jumps up into the sky and won't come down.  Then when she leaves the game and starts the level again it hasn't even registered the butterflies she collected.  The bug probably happens any time you jump at the very end of the level after crossing the 'finish line'. Another issue is the button that resets the games memory (and you have to start over) should not be so easily accessible (it should be hidden better or have some kind of adult only safeguard). My daughter (age 4) once reset her progress accidentally when she was exploring the settings and lost everything!

*AVOID THIS GAME*  I purchased the app as it is supposed to be compatible with Android TV. I loaded it to a Nexus Player and an ADT-1. The game loaded  on both devices and that's about all it did.  The game doesn't respond to inputs from game controllers, keyboards or most and the android TV remote buttons. Basically it responds to the select and back buttons and that's it. It is the same on both devices no matter what control device you use. This renders a game I paid for completely unplayable.   Others have reported getting no replies from the developer regarding issues with this game.  The Dev has not responded to a one-star review I left several days ago and has yet reply to a direct email.  Seriously, who releases and sells an Android TV game without making sure the freaking controllers actually work? There should be a mechanism for reporting fraud to Google.  This game is garbage and I strongly urge you guys not to buy it.
